dataset.title: Plant species list for Niwot Ridge/Green Lakes Valley, 1970 - ongoing.

abstract.para: A plant species list was created for Niwot Ridge and Green Lakes Valley from species identified in those areas by NWT scientists, working primarily at the Saddle and Martinelli sites. Additions to this list included species identified by Komarkova (1979) in the Indian Peaks Wilderness area but not on Niwot Ridge or in the Green Lakes Valley because of the likelihood that those species might exist within the LTER research area. Additions to the list were also provided by Terry Theodose, Leeanne Lestak, Teresa Nettleton, Susan Sherrod, Laura Mujica-Crapanzano (2004), and Hope Humphries. The list was revised to remove duplicate entries, correct typos, and resolve synonomy problems. Species and non-species categories received USDA PLANTS database names and codes.

taxonomicClassification.taxonRankValue: Dead Festuca species and possibly other grasses

description.para: The original iteration of this file was developed from materials provided to Susan Kindig by Marilyn Walker in late March/early April 1993. Those materials were (1) a Saddle/Martinelli site species list developed from species that were identified during LTER years and (2) Komarkova (1979).[SEK 15 April 93] This file was put under sccs control on 19 April 1993.[RCI 19 April 1993] Three additions to the list were supplied by Terry Theodose and were appended to the data section on 4 February 1994.[RCI 4 February 1994] Addition of 2 columns (one containing the 6-character plant species code and the other containing a numeric plant species code) was initiated on 21 March 1994. This work was completed on 24 March 1994.[RCI 21 March 1994] Additions to the list were supplied by Terry Theodose in mid-August of 1994 and they were appended to the data section on 30 August 1994.[RCI 30 August 1994] Additions to the list were supplied by Leanne Lestak following the 1995 field season and were inserted into the data and comments sections where appropriate on 29 November 1995. A correction concerning the numeric species code number for UNKDIC was also corrected on 29 November 1995.[MAH 29 November 1995] Another addition to the list supplied by Leanne Lestak following the 1995 field season was inserted into the data section on 13 December 1995.[MAH 13 December 1995] Two additions to the list were provided by Leanne Lestak and inserted into the data section on 27 February 1996.[MAH 27 February 1996] Two species that had been previously identified but not given numeric species codes were given numeric codes on 13 November 1996.[MAH 13 November 1996] Additions to the list were supplied by Teresa Nettleton and Susan Sherrod following the 1997 field season and were inserted into the data and comments section where appropriate on 8 December 1997.[MAH 8 December 1997] The code for CLAPOC was corrected from 289 to 298, and UNKGSC was added to the unknowns on 14 January 1998.[MAH 14 January 1998] Appended Korb,Kooiman,Marr species list, and corrected spelling of some species.[TMA 25 September 2002] Changed CLERHO ID to 62 from 111, as 111 was already used by SEDRHO.[TMA 19 April 2005] Changed CLERHO back to 111 as it is the synonmym for Sedum rhodanthum (SEDRHO).[TMA 11 September 2007] List completely revised with species additions, corrections to original numbers, codes, and names, and addition of USDA PLANTS database codes and names.[HCH 11 June 2008]

section.para: The initial list included species that were identified in the Green Lakes Valley or on Niwot Ridge by LTER scientists and/or by Komarkova (1979). A second list contained species that might exist in those areas (because they were identified in the Indian Peaks Wilderness area immediately surrounding the NWT LTER research area by Komarkova (1979) but that have not been specifically identified there. Species identified by Marr (1961), Kooiman and Linhart (1981) and Korb (1996) for the four-site Front Range elevation gradient were also included. Additions to the list were provided by Terry Theodose, Leeanne Lestak, Teresa Nettleton, Susan Sherrod, Laura Mujica-Crapanzano (2004) and Hope Humphries. These lists were found to contain typos, duplicate names, codes, and numbers, as well as inconsistencies in synonomy. Therefore, the list was revised to correct these problems and to assign USDA PLANTS names and codes in addition to the original names, codes, and numbers based on Weber and Wittmann (2000). The USDA PLANTS database was selected as the source for names and codes because of its consistency, widespread use, and inclusion of non-species categories. Notes on name selection for those species not the USDA PLANTS database are available from Hope Humphries. The following species and non-species categories not present in the USDA PLANTS database were assigned USDA-like codes: code name 2DEADD Dead Deschampsia caespitosa 2DEADF Dead Festuca species and possibly other grasses 2DEADK Dead Kobresia myosuroides 2DECMA Decomposed mat 2GENT Gentianaceae species 2HOLE Hole 2NSL No vegetation in second layer 2NTL No vegetation in third layer 2SCAT Scat 2SCATE Elk scat 2TROU Trough 2UNK Unknown 2UNK Unknown 2UNKCL Unknown crustose lichen 2UNKCU Unknown cushion 2UNKFM Unknown forb mat 2UNKGM Unknown graminoid mat 2UNKGS Unknown grey soil crust 2UNKLG Light green soil crust 2UNKMA Unknown mat 2UNKML Unknown moss/lichen 2UNKMU Unknown mustard 2UNKSC Unknown soil crust 2X Registration marker for point quadrat frame LEAR99 Lecanora armeniaca LERU99 Lecanora rupestris STCU99 Stereocaulon cumulatum
